frameDefinitions: An Entity began its existence in the context of a location of Origin, which is a discourse-salient place, or culture.
A Current_country is identified as matching or not matching the instance of the Discourse_salient_country.
A Trajector is identified as occurring at the same time as some better-known Landmark.
An Entity changes from one kind of thing (Initial_category) to another kind of thing (Final_category).
An Entity is presented as having been seen or experienced by a (typically generic and backgrounded)
An Entity is obscure, unnotable, and in general little-known.

listRoleDefinitions: The item whose <fen>Origin</fen> is under discussion.
The discourse-salient place or culture where the <fen>Entity</fen> was produced.
The country or countries that the speaker is indicating in the current instance, which may match or be distinct from the <fen>Discourse_salient_country</fen>.

The country that has been featured in the discourse, or that the speaker/hearer identify with or are located in; it serves to identify the <fen>Current_country</fen> by specifying it as the same or different.  This role is incorporated in the targets of this frame.
The entity that occurs at some time.
The event which designates the time at which a trajector occurs.
The period that occurs with respect to some other time.
The period in which a trajector takes place.  This period can be cyclical and, in that case, is interpreted contextually.
The event that occurs at some time.
The entity which designates the time of some trajector.  Note: this role is infrequent or non-existent in English and is included for completeness.
The concrete or abstract entity that undergoes a change.
The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that results from the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> belongs to before it undergoes the change.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> undergoes the transformation.
The location that the change takes place.
A concrete thing or abstract phenomenon or fact that is assessed in terms of how well recognizable it is to a <fen>Cognizer</fen>.
The (typically non-specific and backgrounded) sentient being for whom the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses a specified level of recognizability.
The deviation of the actual level of recognizability of the <fen>Entity</fen> from the level specified by the target.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is not widely known and rather obscure.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is not well known.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is not famous.
